```console 
$ curl http://0.0.0.0:5000/api/records/1
{
  "created": "Fri, 11 Dec 2015 12:42:46 GMT", 
  "id": "1", 
  "links": {
    "self": "http://0.0.0.0:5000/api/records/1"
  }, 
  "metadata": {
    "title": "Invenio 3 rocks"
  }, 
  "revision": 1, 
  "updated": "Fri, 11 Dec 2015 12:42:46 GMT"
}
```

The provided date format is human-oriented, while it would be better to use machine-oriented ISO 8601 Z format in the APIs.  Example: `2015-05-26T11:00:00Z`.

For inspiration, see how we addresed this in ClaimStore:
- issue: https://github.com/inveniosoftware/claimstore/issues/6
- implementation: https://github.com/inveniosoftware/claimstore/pull/29

